@author Element Finance
 @title Wrapped Position Core

@dev Makes the actual deposit into the 'vault'
 @return Tuple (shares minted, amount underlying used)

@dev Makes the actual withdraw from the 'vault'
 @return returns the amount produced

params.account: The account which will be approve to transfer tokens
params.amount: The approval amount, if set to uint256.max the allowance does not go down on transfers.

returns._0: returns true for compatibility with the ERC20 standard
The underlying token balance of the address

params._token: The underlying token.               This token should revert in the event of a transfer failure.

params._amount: The amount of underlying tokens to deposit

returns._0: Returns the number of Wrapped Position tokens minted

params._shares: Shares to calculate underlying value for

returns._0: The value of underlying assets for the given shares

permit(address,address,uint256,uint256,u.details: The signature for this function follows EIP 712 standard and should be generated with the      eth_signTypedData JSON RPC call instead of the eth_sign JSON RPC call. If using out of date      parity signing libraries the v component may need to be adjusted. Also it is very rare but possible      for v to be other values, those values are not supported.

params.deadline: the timestamp which the signature must be submitted by to be valid
params.owner: the owner of the account which is having the new approval set
params.r: The r component of the ECDSA signature
params.s: The s component of the ECDSA signature
params.spender: the address which will be allowed to spend owner's tokens
params.v: Extra ECDSA data which allows public key recovery from signature assumed to be 27 or 28

prefundedDeposit(address).details: WARNING - The call which funds this method MUST be in the same transaction

returns._0: Returns (WP tokens minted, used underlying,                  senders WP balance before mint)

transfer(address,uint256).details: transfers to this contract address or 0 will fail

params.amount: The amount user token to send
params.recipient: The address which will be credited with the tokens

returns._0: returns true on success, reverts on failure so cannot return false.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: will fail transfers which send funds to this contract or 0

params.amount: the number of tokens to send
params.recipient: The destination of the ERC20 tokens
params.spender: The source of the ERC20 tokens

returns._0: returns true on success and reverts on failure

params._destination: The address which is credited with tokens
params._minUnderlying: The min output the caller expects
params._shares: The amount of shares the user is burning to withdraw underlying

returns._0: The amount of underlying transferred to the destination

params._amount: The amount of underlying to try to redeem for
params._destination: The address to send the output to

returns._0: The amount of underlying released, and shares used

approve(address,uint256).notice: This function allows a user to approve an account which can transfer         tokens on their behalf.

balanceOfUnderlying(address).notice: Get the underlying balance of an address

deposit(address,uint256).notice: Entry point to deposit tokens into the Wrapped Position contract         Transfers tokens on behalf of caller so the caller must set         allowance on the contract prior to call.

getSharesToUnderlying(uint256).notice: Returns the amount of the underlying asset a certain amount of shares is worth

permit(address,address,uint256,uint256,u.notice: This function allows a caller who is not the owner of an account to execute the functionality of 'approve' with the owners signature.

prefundedDeposit(address).notice: Entry point to deposit tokens into the Wrapped Position contract         Assumes the tokens were transferred before this was called

transfer(address,uint256).notice: Allows a token owner to send tokens to another address

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Transfers an amount of erc20 from a spender to a receipt

withdraw(address,uint256,uint256).notice: Exit point to withdraw tokens from the Wrapped Position contract

withdrawUnderlying(address,uint256,uint2.notice: This function burns enough tokens from the sender to send _amount          of underlying to the _destination.
